trans-unit.source: Provides the base class for implementing a CodeDOM-based designer loader.
trans-unit.target: Gir basisklassen for å implementere en CodeDOM kodebasert designer laster.

trans-unit.source: CodeDomDesignerLoader is an abstract class that provides a full designer loader based on the Code Document Object Model (CodeDOM).
trans-unit.target: CodeDomDesignerLoader er en abstrakt klasse som gir en hel designer laster basert på kode dokumentobjektmodellen (CodeDOM).

trans-unit.source: You provide the CodeDOM parser and generator, and a type resolution service.
trans-unit.target: Du kan angi CodeDOM-parseren og generatoren, og en type løsning.

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader"></xref> class.
trans-unit.target: Initialiserer en ny forekomst av den <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader"> </xref> klasse.

trans-unit.source: Gets the CodeDomProvider this designer loader will use.
trans-unit.target: Henter CodeDomProvider denne designer laster bruker.

trans-unit.source: The designer loader does not parse or generate code from the returned CodeDomProvider, but it does use the provider to obtain an <xref:System.CodeDom.Compiler.ICodeGenerator> that it can use to validate identifiers in the name-creation service.
trans-unit.target: Designer-laster ikke analysere eller generere kode fra returnerte CodeDomProvider, men den bruker leverandøren ikke hente en <xref:System.CodeDom.Compiler.ICodeGenerator>den kan bruke til å validere identifikatorer i tjenesten name-creation.</xref:System.CodeDom.Compiler.ICodeGenerator>

trans-unit.source: The designer loader will also check the CodeDomProvider to see if it implements the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.ICodeDomDesignerReload> interface.
trans-unit.target: Designer-laster sjekker også CodeDomProvider for å se om den implementerer den <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.ICodeDomDesignerReload>grensesnittet.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.ICodeDomDesignerReload>

trans-unit.source: For more information on parsing or generating code, see the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Parse%2A> and <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Write%2A> methods.
trans-unit.target: For mer informasjon om analyse eller kodegenerering, kan du se den <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Parse%2A>og <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Write%2A>metoder.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Write%2A> </xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Parse%2A>

trans-unit.source: The CodeDomProvider this designer loader will use
trans-unit.target: CodeDomProvider denne designer laster bruker

trans-unit.source: Releases the resources used by the <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader"></xref> class.
trans-unit.target: Frigir ressursene som brukes av den <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader"> </xref> klasse.

trans-unit.source: The Dispose method removes services added by the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Initialize%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Fjerningsmetoden fjerner tjenester som er lagt til av den <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Initialize%2A>metoden.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Initialize%2A>

trans-unit.source: Call Dispose when you are finished using the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>.
trans-unit.target: Kall avhending når du er ferdig med <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>

trans-unit.source: The Dispose method leaves the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader> in an unusable state.
trans-unit.target: Fjerningsmetoden forlater den <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>i en ubrukelig tilstand.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>

trans-unit.source: After calling Dispose, you must release all references to the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader> so the garbage collector can reclaim the memory that the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader> was occupying.
trans-unit.target: Etter å avhending, må du frigi alle referanser til den <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>Slik saneringsoppsamlingen kan gjenvinne minnet som den <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>ble bruker.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader> </xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>

trans-unit.source: For more information, see [Cleaning Up Unmanaged Resources](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md) and [Implementing a Dispose Method](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil ha mer informasjon, se [Rydder opp uforvaltede ressurser](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md) og [implementere metoden fjerne](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > Always call Dispose before you release your last reference to the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Alltid kall fjerne før du slipper siste referanse til <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>

trans-unit.source: Otherwise, the resources it is using will not be freed until the garbage collector calls the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader> object's `Finalize` method.
trans-unit.target: Ellers ressurser den bruker vil ikke bli frigjort før saneringsoppsamling kall av <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>objektets `Finalize` metode.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>

trans-unit.source: Initializes services.
trans-unit.target: Initialiserer services.

trans-unit.source: The following table describes the replaceable services that the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader> adds to the service container.
trans-unit.target: Tabellen nedenfor beskriver de kan erstattes services som den <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>legger til i beholderen.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>

trans-unit.source: |Term|Definition| |----------|----------------| |<xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.INameCreationService>|Provides semantics for creating names of objects.
trans-unit.target: | Perioden | Definisjonen | |----------|----------------| | <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.INameCreationService>| Gir semantikk for oppretting av navn på objekter.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.INameCreationService>

trans-unit.source: The service uses the CodeDOM provider’s <xref:System.CodeDom.Compiler.ICodeGenerator> interface to create names that are valid identifiers for the language.
trans-unit.target: Tjenesten bruker CodeDOM leverandørens <xref:System.CodeDom.Compiler.ICodeGenerator>grensesnittet til å opprette navn er gyldige identifikatorer for språket.</xref:System.CodeDom.Compiler.ICodeGenerator>

trans-unit.source: In addition, the name creation service supports empty names.
trans-unit.target: Tjenesten navnet oppretting støtter i tillegg tomme navn.

trans-unit.source: Empty names should be interpreted as temporary local variables during serialization.| |<xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerSerializationService>|Allows other objects to serialize a group of components into a binary object.
trans-unit.target: Tomme navn kan tolkes som en midlertidig lokale variabler under serialisering. | | <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerSerializationService>| Tillater at andre objekter til å serialisere en gruppe av komponentene til en binær objekt.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerSerializationService>

trans-unit.source: This service is most often used by features such as copy and paste or undo and redo.
trans-unit.target: Denne tjenesten brukes vanligvis av funksjoner for eksempel Kopier og Lim inn eller angre og gjør om.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader> class provides a designer serialization service that is based on creating CodeDOM trees for objects.| |<xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.ComponentSerializationService>|This service replaces <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerSerializationService> as a means to serialize components to a binary object.| For details on replaceable and non-replaceable services, see <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.BasicDesignerLoader>.
trans-unit.target: Klassen <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>er en designer serialisering-tjeneste som er basert på oppretter CodeDOM trær for objekter. | | <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.ComponentSerializationService>| Denne tjenesten erstatter <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerSerializationService>å serialisere komponentene til en binær objekt. | For informasjon om kan erstattes og ikke kan erstattes, kan du se <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.BasicDesignerLoader>.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.BasicDesignerLoader> </xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerSerializationService> </xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.ComponentSerializationService> </xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>

trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderHost"> </xref> har ikke blitt initialisert, eller designer-laster ikke angir en type oppløsning tjeneste som kreves for løsningstjeneste.

trans-unit.source: Returns a value indicating whether a reload is required.
trans-unit.target: Returnerer en verdi som angir om en Last er nødvendig.

trans-unit.source: The IsReloadNeeded method checks for the presence of the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.ICodeDomDesignerReload> interface on the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.CodeDomProvider%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Metoden IsReloadNeeded ser etter <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.ICodeDomDesignerReload>grensesnitt for <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.CodeDomProvider%2A>.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.CodeDomProvider%2A> </xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.ICodeDomDesignerReload>

trans-unit.source: The provider will reparse the CodeDOM tree and pass the resulting parse tree to the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.ICodeDomDesignerReload.ShouldReloadDesigner%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Leverandøren skal ny analyse treet CodeDOM og sende resulterende spaltes treet til den <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.ICodeDomDesignerReload.ShouldReloadDesigner%2A>metoden.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.ICodeDomDesignerReload.ShouldReloadDesigner%2A>

trans-unit.source: If this method returns `false`, the designer will not be reloaded.
trans-unit.target: Hvis denne metoden returnerer `false`, designer kan ikke lastes inn på nytt.

trans-unit.source: The Parse method is called when the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader> needs to parse the source code.
trans-unit.target: Metoden spaltes kalles når den <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>må analysere kildekoden.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>

trans-unit.target: Plasseringen til datakilden kode og formatet må være angitt av avledes klasser.

trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeCompileUnit"> </xref> fra en spaltes-operasjon.

trans-unit.source: Requests serialization of the root component of the designer.
trans-unit.target: Forespørsler serialisering av komponenten roten av designer.

trans-unit.source: The PerformFlush method obtains the root <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomSerializer> for the root component of the designer and invokes the serializer to serialize the component.
trans-unit.target: Metoden PerformFlush anskaffer roten <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomSerializer>for komponenten roten av designer og aktiverer serialiseringen for å serialisere komponenten.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomSerializer>

trans-unit.source: If the result of this operation is a <xref:System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration>, then PerformFlush integrates the <xref:System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration> with the existing CodeDOM tree.
trans-unit.target: Hvis resultatet av denne operasjonen er en <xref:System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration>, og deretter PerformFlush integrerer den <xref:System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration>med eksisterende CodeDOM tre.</xref:System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration> </xref:System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration>

trans-unit.source: The result is the original CodeDOM tree with matching members and statements replaced.
trans-unit.target: Resultatet er opprinnelige CodeDOM treet med samsvarende medlemmer og setninger erstattes.

trans-unit.source: Finally, PerformFlush calls the abstract <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Write%2A> method to save this CodeDOM tree.
trans-unit.target: Til slutt PerformFlush kaller abstract <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Write%2A>metode for å lagre dette CodeDOM treet.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Write%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the serialization of the root designer component does not result in a <xref:System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration>, then PerformFlush does nothing further.
trans-unit.target: Hvis serialisering av komponenten roten designer ikke resulterer i en <xref:System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration>, og deretter PerformFlush gjøre noe mer.</xref:System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration>

trans-unit.source: > [!IMPORTANT] > It is the responsibility of the caller to ensure that a CodeDOM originates from a trusted source.
trans-unit.target: > [!IMPORTANT] > Er ansvarlig for oppkalleren å sikre at en CodeDOM stammer fra en pålitelig kilde.

trans-unit.source: Accepting a CodeDOM object from an untrusted party could allow that party to run malicious code.
trans-unit.target: Godta et CodeDOM objekt fra en uklarert part føre til at tredjeparter å kjøre skadelig kode.

trans-unit.source: When flushing a CodeDOM into a file, the framework will run code represented by the CodeDOM object and the serialized content of the object as provided.
trans-unit.target: Når tømming CodeDOM i en fil, kjøres rammeverket kode som er representert av CodeDOM-objektet og serialiserte innholdet i objektet som er oppgitt.

trans-unit.source: The PerformLoad method obtains an <xref:System.CodeDom.Compiler.ICodeParser> from the CodeDOM provider and parses the code.
trans-unit.target: Metoden PerformLoad henter en <xref:System.CodeDom.Compiler.ICodeParser>fra leverandøren CodeDOM og analyserer koden.</xref:System.CodeDom.Compiler.ICodeParser>

trans-unit.source: PerformLoad locates the first class in the file, obtains a root <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomSerializer> for the data type, and then invokes the serializer to deserialize the data type.
trans-unit.target: PerformLoad finner første klassen i filen, henter en rot <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomSerializer>for datatypen, og aktiverer serialiseringen for å deserialisere datatypen.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomSerializer>

trans-unit.source: PerformLoad assumes that this process will create all necessary components in the <xref:System.ComponentModel.IContainer> of the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.BasicDesignerLoader.LoaderHost%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: PerformLoad antar at denne prosessen oppretter alle nødvendige komponenter i den <xref:System.ComponentModel.IContainer>av den <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.BasicDesignerLoader.LoaderHost%2A>egenskapen.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.BasicDesignerLoader.LoaderHost%2A> </xref:System.ComponentModel.IContainer>

trans-unit.source: Finally, PerformLoad calls the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.BasicDesignerLoader.SetBaseComponentClassName%2A> method with the fully qualified name of the type it passed to the CodeDOM serializer.
trans-unit.target: Til slutt PerformLoad kaller den <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.BasicDesignerLoader.SetBaseComponentClassName%2A>metoden med typen som det ble sendt til CodeDOM serialiseringen fullstendig kvalifisert navn.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.BasicDesignerLoader.SetBaseComponentClassName%2A>

trans-unit.source: Gets the type resolution service to be used with this designer loader.
trans-unit.target: Henter typen oppløsning service som skal brukes med denne designer laster.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader> automatically adds this <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.ITypeResolutionService> to the service container when the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Initialize%2A> method is invoked.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>automatisk legges <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.ITypeResolutionService>til beholderen når den <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Initialize%2A>metoden aktiveres.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Initialize%2A> </xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.ITypeResolutionService> </xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>

trans-unit.source: While the type resolution service is optional in many scenarios, it is required for code interpretation because source code contains type names, but no assembly references.
trans-unit.target: Typen oppløsning service er valgfrie i mange situasjoner, er obligatorisk for koden tolkning fordi kildekode inneholder type navn, men ingen refererer til samlingen.

trans-unit.source: An <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.ITypeResolutionService"></xref> that the CodeDOM serializers will use when resolving types.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.ITypeResolutionService"> </xref> at CodeDOM serializers brukes til å løse typer.

trans-unit.source: Writes compile-unit changes to persistent storage.
trans-unit.target: Skriver kompilering enhet endringer til vedvarende lager.

trans-unit.source: The Write method saves a <xref:System.CodeDom.CodeCompileUnit> to persistent storage.
trans-unit.target: Write-metoden lagrer en <xref:System.CodeDom.CodeCompileUnit>til vedvarende lager.</xref:System.CodeDom.CodeCompileUnit>

trans-unit.source: The deriving class is responsible for invoking the <xref:System.CodeDom.Compiler.ICodeGenerator> on the appropriate text writer to save the code.
trans-unit.target: Klassen deriving er ansvarlig for aktivering av <xref:System.CodeDom.Compiler.ICodeGenerator>på den riktige tekstskriver lagre koden.</xref:System.CodeDom.Compiler.ICodeGenerator>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader> ensures that the CodeDOM objects that are passed to Write are the same instances of objects that were retrieved from <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Parse%2A>, except in cases where the serialization process had to make changes to the code.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>sikrer at CodeDOM objektene som er sendt til skriving er de samme forekomstene av objekter som ble hentet fra <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Parse%2A>, unntatt i tilfeller der serialisering prosessen måtte gjøre endringer i koden.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader.Parse%2A> </xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.CodeDomDesignerLoader>

trans-unit.source: This allows an optimized designer loader to store additional data in the <xref:System.CodeDom.CodeObject.UserData%2A> property of code elements.
trans-unit.target: Dette gjør det mulig for en minneoptimaliserte designer laster til å lagre flere data i den <xref:System.CodeDom.CodeObject.UserData%2A>egenskapen code-elementer.</xref:System.CodeDom.CodeObject.UserData%2A>

trans-unit.source: This data will be available during the Write method for any elements that were not replaced by the serialization process.
trans-unit.target: Disse dataene vil være tilgjengelig under Write-metoden for elementer som ikke ble erstattet av prosessen for serialisering.
